16 SECTION 6.(b) G.S. 106-805 reads as rewritten:
17 "§ 106-805. Written notice of swine farms.
18 Any person who intends to construct a swine farm whose animal waste management system
19 is subject to a permit under Part 1 or 1A Part 1A of Article 21 of Chapter 143 of the General
20 Statutes shall, after completing a site evaluation and before the farm site is modified, notify all
21 adjoining property owners; all property owners who own property located across a public road,
22 street, or highway from the swine farm; the county or counties in which the farm site is located;
23 and the local health department or departments having jurisdiction over the farm site of that
24 person's intent to construct the swine farm. This notice shall be by certified mail sent to the
25 address on record at the property tax office in the county in which the land is located. Notice to
26 a county shall be sent to the county manager or, if there is no county manager, to the chair of the
27 board of county commissioners. Notice to a local health department shall be sent to the local
28 health director. The written notice shall include all of the following:
29 (1) The name and address of the person intending to construct a swine farm.
30 (2) The type of swine farm and the design capacity of the animal waste
31 management system.
32 (3) The name and address of the technical specialist preparing the waste
33 management plan.
34 (4) The address of the local Soil and Water Conservation District office.
35 (5) Information informing the adjoining property owners and the property owners
36 who own property located across a public road, street, or highway from the
37 swine farm that they may submit written comments to the Division of Water
38 Resources, Department of Environmental Quality."
