10 MODIFY REQUIREMENTS FOR COMPOSTING OF EQUINE AND BOVINE
11 MORTALITY
12 SECTION 9.(a) Definitions. – For purposes of this section, "Disposal Systems Rule"
13 means 15A NCAC 02T .0113 (Permitting By Regulation).
14 SECTION 9.(b) Disposal Systems Rule. – Until the effective date of the revised
15 permanent rules that the Environmental Management Commission is required to adopt pursuant
16 to subsection (d) of this section, the Commission shall implement the Disposal Systems Rule as
17 provided in subsection (c) of this section.
18 SECTION 9.(c) Implementation. – Notwithstanding any provision of Subchapter
19 02T of Title 15A of the North Carolina Administrative Code, and in addition to all disposal
20 systems permitted by regulation pursuant to subsection (a) of the Disposal Systems Rule on the
21 date this section becomes effective, the Environmental Management Commission shall also deem
22 a disposal system to be permitted pursuant to G.S. 143-215.1(b) and not require individual
23 permits or coverage under a general permit if the disposal system meets all of the following
24 criteria:
25 (1) The disposal system is used for equine or bovine composting.
26 (2) The disposal system does not result in any violations of surface water or
27 groundwater standards.
28 (3) The disposal system does not directly discharge to surface waters.
29 (4) The construction and operation of facilities, if any are included in the disposal
30 system, are approved by the North Carolina Department of Agriculture and
31 Consumer Services.
32 (5) The disposal system is approved by the State Veterinarian pursuant to
33 G.S. 106-403.
34 (6) In the event of an imminent threat of a contagious animal disease, any
35 emergency measure or procedure related to composting of animal mortality
36 pursuant to G.S. 106-399.4(a) is authorized.
37 SECTION 9.(d) Additional Rulemaking Authority. – The Commission shall adopt
38 a rule to amend the Disposal Systems Rule consistent with subsection (c) of this section.
39 Notwithstanding G.S. 150B-19(4), the amendment to the Disposal Systems Rule adopted by the
40 Commission pursuant to this section shall be substantively identical to the provisions of
41 subsection (c) of this section. Rules adopted pursuant to this section are not subject to Part 3 of
42 Article 2A of Chapter 150B of the General Statutes. Rules adopted pursuant to this section shall
43 become effective as provided in G.S. 150B-21.3(b1), as though 10 or more written objections
44 had been received as provided in G.S. 150B-21.3(b2).
45 SECTION 9.(e) Sunset. – This section expires when permanent rules adopted as
46 required by subsection (d) of this section become effective.
