11 (1) Religious observance. – A minimum of two excused absences each academic
12 year for religious observances required by the faith of a student or the student's
13 parent or legal guardian.
14 (2) Military leave. – A minimum of two excused absences each academic year, if
15 all of the following conditions are met:
16 a. The student's parent or legal guardian is an active duty member of the
17 uniformed services, as defined by Article 29B of this Chapter, the
18 Interstate Compact on Educational Opportunity for Military Children.
19 b. The student's parent or legal guardian has been called to duty for, is on
20 leave from, or has immediately returned from deployment to a combat
21 zone or combat support posting.
22 c. The student is not identified by the local school administrative unit as
23 at risk of academic failure because of unexcused absences.
24 (3) Equestrian and agricultural events. – A minimum of two excused absences
25 each academic year for participation in equestrian sporting events, livestock
26 shows, or similar agricultural events.
27 The rules may require that the student's parent or legal guardian give the principal written
28 notice of the request for an excused absence a reasonable time prior to the religious observance
29 or military leave. observance, military leave, or equestrian and agricultural event. The student
30 shall be given the opportunity to make up any tests or other work missed due to an excused
31 absence for a religious observance or military leave.
32 (c) It shall be the duty of all school officials to carry out such instructions from the State
33 Board of Education, and any school official failing to carry out such instructions shall be guilty
34 of a Class 3 misdemeanor: Provided, that the compulsory attendance law herein prescribed shall
35 not be in force in any local school administrative unit that has a higher compulsory attendance
