7 SECTION 12. G.S. 143-442 reads as rewritten:
8 "§ 143-442. Registration.
9 (a) Every pesticide prior to being distributed, sold, or offered for sale within this State or
10 delivered for transportation or transported in intrastate commerce or between points within this
11 State through any point outside this State shall be registered in the office of the Board, and such
12 registration shall be renewed annually before January 1 for the ensuing calendar year. Beginning
13 in 1988, the Board may by rule adopt a system of staggered three-year registrations. The applicant
14 for registration shall file with the Board a statement that includes all of the following:
15 (1) The name and address of the applicant and the name and address of the person
16 whose name will appear on the label, if other than the applicant.
17 (2) The name of the pesticide.
18 (3) A complete copy of the labeling accompanying the pesticide and a statement
19 of all claims to be made for it including directions for use.
20 (4) If requested by the Board, a full description of the tests made and the results
21 thereof upon which the claims are based.
22 (5) In the case of renewal of registration, a statement with respect to information
23 which is different from that furnished when the pesticide was last registered.
24 (6) Repealed by Session Laws 2011-239, s. 1, effective June 23, 2011, and
25 applicable to applications for registration or renewals of registration filed on
26 or after that date.
27 (7) Any other information needed by the Board to determine the amount of annual
28 assessment payable by the applicant.
29 (b) The applicant shall pay an annual registration fee of one hundred fifty dollars
30 ($150.00) plus an additional annual assessment for each brand or grade of pesticide registered.
31 The annual assessment shall be fifty dollars ($50.00) if the applicant's gross sales of the pesticide
32 in this State for the preceding 12 months for the period ending September 30th were more than
33 five thousand dollars ($5,000.00) and twenty-five dollars ($25.00) if gross sales were less than
34 five thousand dollars ($5,000.00). set by the Board, not to exceed one hundred twenty-five dollars
35 ($125.00). An additional two hundred dollars ($200.00) delinquent registration penalty shall be
36 assessed against the registrant for each brand or grade of pesticide which is marketed in North
37 Carolina prior to registration as required by this Article. In the case of multi-year registration, the
38 annual fee and additional assessment for each year shall be paid at the time of the initial
39 registration. The Board shall give a pro rata refund of the registration fee and additional
40 assessment to the registrant in the event that registration is canceled by the Board or by the United
41 States Environmental Protection Agency.
42 …."
