21 REDUCE PENALTY FOR CERTAIN SHELLFISH AQUACULTURE VIOLATIONS
22 SECTION 16.(a) G.S. 113-187 reads as rewritten:
23 "§ 113-187. Penalties for violations of Subchapter and rules.
24 (a) Any person who participates in a commercial fishing operation conducted in violation
25 of any provision of this Subchapter and its implementing rules or in an operation in connection
26 with which any vessel is used in violation of any provision of this Subchapter and its
27 implementing rules is guilty of a Class A1 misdemeanor.
28 (b) Any owner of a vessel who knowingly permits it to be used in violation of any
29 provision of this Subchapter and its implementing rules is guilty of a Class A1 misdemeanor.
30 (c) Any person in charge of a commercial fishing operation conducted in violation of any
31 provision of this Subchapter and its implementing rules or in charge of any vessel used in
32 violation of any provision of this Subchapter and its implementing rules is guilty of a Class A1
33 misdemeanor.
34 (d) Any person in charge of a commercial fishing operation conducted in violation of the
35 following provisions of this Subchapter or the following rules of the Marine Fisheries
36 Commission; and any person in charge of any vessel used in violation of the following provisions
37 of the Subchapter or the following rules, shall be guilty of a Class A1 misdemeanor. The
38 violations of the statute or the rules for which the penalty is mandatory are:
39 (1) Taking or attempting to take, possess, sell, or offer for sale any oysters,
40 mussels, or clams taken from areas closed by statute, rule, or proclamation
41 because of suspected pollution.
42 (2) Taking or attempting to take or have in possession aboard a vessel, shrimp
43 taken by the use of a trawl net, in areas not opened to shrimping, pulled by a
44 vessel not showing lights required by G.S. 75A-6 after sunset and before
45 sunrise.
46 (3) Using a trawl net in any coastal fishing waters closed by proclamation or rule
47 to trawl nets.
48 (4) Violating the provisions of a special permit or gear license issued by the
49 Department.
